<br>
Servers go down for maintenance Wednesday morning. I think it would be fun to raid Naggy that evening, and depending on enthusiasm, Vox on Thursday? I want to start gathering people at 6:30, and will start going in once we have a few groups powerful enough to start clearing the way. Please contact me in game, on this post, or by email Indromeda@one.net if you are interested in going. I especially am interested in finding a few people to help guide and pull. I am not turning away 53+ people who can benefit this raid, and you can also get in on the rolls.<br>
<br>
Loot: I would like dibs on one item of my choice, and the rest will be randomed as follows: All Epic items will be rolled on by the class present. Period. All other items will be rolled by any class that can use it. You may roll on every item that you can use, however, you can only win ONE item. I will track the top 5 rolls per item, so if you win a “better” item, your first item will be handed to the person who had rolled next highest. I will ask group leaders to track which classes need which no_drop items, and those people will be ressed first, those items get rolled first.<br>
<br>
Death: Expect to die at least once from Naggy, probably multiple times from Vox. Most tanks will die, and with Vox, likely most casters will die. Expect it. If we have enough interest in Vox, I will post strategy info. Naggy is fairly simple, for a dragon.<br>
<br>
Resist Gear: Bring it. Wear it. If you have low resists, you are going to be hindering with lag and wasted heals. Beg/borrow/buy/loan/camp some. Get at least 100 MR, and 100 CR or FR depending on which dragon. Naggy is Fire, Vox is Cold. I will have group leaders checking who has resist gear and who doesn’t. Do your best to get as much as you can.<br>
<br>
Be Early: We will start clearing once I get 2-3 groups. I hate standing around doing nothing. We will stay as busy as possible until we have enough for the dragon. As soon as we have enough manpower, I won't be taking any more people.<br>
<br>
Friends: Friends welcome if they read and agree to the above rules, and know how to conduct themselves during a raid. <br>
